                <div class="container">
                    <div class="row">
                        <h2 class="wow fadeInUp center text-center"> </h2>
                    </div>
                </div>
                <div data-jarallax-element="-150" class="text-section-box"></div>
                <div class="container">
                    <div class="row text-row">
                        <div class="col-lg-6">
                            <div class="text-section-block">
                                <h3>What procedures are often performed after massive weight loss?</h3>
                                <p>If you’re considering plastic surgery after massive weight loss in Houston, there are a variety of procedures that can be combined to give you the body you’ve always wanted.</p>
                            </div>
                            <div class="text-section-block">
                                <h3>Tummy Tuck</h3>
                                <p>
                                    Sagging skin after massive weight loss is very common in the abdominal area, as this is the location where most people carry excess weight. An abdominoplasty, more commonly referred to as a <a href="/houston-tummy-tucks">tummy tuck</a>, can be the perfect solution. During the procedure, your plastic surgeon can remove excess skin, tighten abdominal muscles and redistribute fat to give you the body shape you want.
                                </p>
                            </div>
                            <div class="text-section-block">
                                <h3>Arm Lift</h3>
                                <p>
                                    Also called a brachioplasty, an <a href="/arm-lift-houston">arm lift procedure</a> will remove excess skin from the upper arm and tighten and smooth the underlying supportive tissues. The result will be well-shaped arms that you can be proud to show off.
                                </p>
                            </div>
                            <div class="text-section-block">
                                <h3>Thigh Lift</h3>
                                <p>
                                    <a href="/thigh-lift-houston">A thigh lift</a> removes excess skin on the inner thigh that results from massive weight loss. The procedure will tighten and firm the areas of the upper thigh and help you achieve the sleek, contoured look you’re looking for.
                                </p>
                            </div>
                            <div class="text-section-block">
                                <h3>Lower Body Lift</h3>
                                <p>
                                    A <a href="/lipectomy-houston">lower body lift</a>, also called a belt lipectomy, is a plastic surgery procedure that reshapes the lower body, including areas of the hips, thighs, and buttocks. The surgery can include the removal of excess skin, liposuction of fat deposits and the tightening of muscle groups to give a more sleek and defined shape.
                                </p>
                            </div>
                        </div>

                        <div class="col-lg-6 pt-lg-5">
                            <div class="text-section-block">                               

                                <div class="text-section-block">
                                    <h3>Breasts</h3>
                                    <p class="align-content-end">
                                        As breasts are composed primarily of fatty tissue, they can undergo many changes during massive weight loss. In some cases, breasts may start to severely sag. Maybe you would prefer them to be larger or smaller to fit better with your new body shape. <a href="/breast-augmentation-houston">Breast augmentations</a>, <a href="/breast-reduction-houston">breast reductions</a>, and <a href="/breast-lift-surgery-houston">breast lifts</a> are all common components of plastic surgery after massive weight loss.
                                    </p>
                                </div>
                            </div>
                            <div class="text-section-block">
                                <h3>What to expect at your initial consultation for plastic surgery after massive weight loss in Houstony?</h3>
                                <p class="align-content-end">
                                    If you are interested in plastic surgery after massive weight loss in Houston, Texas, you can contact the clinic to schedule a consultation today. You can expect the initial consultation to last an hour or more. In your consultation, your TOPS plastic surgeon will:
                                </p>
                                <ul>
                                    <li>Listen to your specific complaints and goals.</li>
                                    <li>Perform a thorough examination, focusing on your individual anatomy. Precise measurements and photographs will be taken.</li>
                                    <li>Your TOPS plastic surgeon will discuss details of the surgical procedures that are offered and which approach is right for you. Details regarding scars and technique will be outlined for you.</li>
                                    <li>If your plastic surgeon feels that your plastic surgery after massive weight loss may be approved by insurance, a letter will be submitted to your insurance asking for insurance approval.</li>
                                    <li>The risks and benefits of the recommended procedures will be thoroughly outlined.</li>
                                    <li>You will be given ample opportunity to ask questions from both your plastic surgeon and the cosmetic staff regarding massive weight loss plastic surgery in Houston.</li>
                                    <li>You will be sent home with a packet of information regarding the procedure, including a detailed consent form and instructions for before and after your Houston plastic surgery after massive weight loss.</li>
                                </ul>
                                <p>
                                    Patients who have undergone massive weight loss have a special set of issues.  Dr. Danielle Andry and Dr. Nandi Wijay trained with one of the innovators in body contouring after massive weight loss and have experience with multiple techniques to specifically meet the needs of this patient population.
                                </p>
